{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 78, "line_start": 78, "page_hint": null, "section": "RESULTS", "text": "The tensile strength for sound cast metal is about $60\\%$ of that for wrought metal."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 95, "line_start": 95, "page_hint": null, "section": "RESULTS", "text": "These data were obtained from short-time stress-rupture tests at temperatures of 1100, 1300, 1500, and $1700^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ and are not suitable for establishing design stresses by conventional techniques."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 95, "line_start": 95, "page_hint": null, "section": "RESULTS", "text": "The Dorn-Shepard parameter<sup>2</sup> has been used to establish a master curve from which 100,000 rupture-stress values may be obtained."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 95, "line_start": 95, "page_hint": null, "section": "RESULTS", "text": "The activation energy, 83,200 cal/mole- ${}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{K}$ , for wrought metal<sup>3</sup> was employed."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 100, "line_start": 100, "page_hint": null, "section": "RESULTS", "text": "Stress values for 100,000 hr obtained from this curve are presented in Table 2 and compared to present MSRE design stresses."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 100, "line_start": 100, "page_hint": null, "section": "RESULTS", "text": "This is true for temperatures above $1150^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 100, "line_start": 100, "page_hint": null, "section": "RESULTS", "text": "Below $1150^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ , however, cast metal design stresses must be based on one fourth of the tensile strength since these stresses will be less than those obtained from stress-rupture data."}
